      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KISS AND RUN (1) had a tricky draw last time and although midfield in fourth wasn't far away finishing 4.5 lengths from the winner (23.15). Has a good winning strike rate at this journey. Can bounce back. SUDDEN SURPRISE (7) drifted back from wide but charged home to hit the frame when 3.5 lengths from the winner (16.08) at this track in Grade 4/5. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from five starts. Expected to be in this for a long way. VOLARE ALTO (3) was fifth in a Grade 4/5 two back then found trouble in the run and took a tumble at this track last time. May be worth another try. REDSHIFT FOXTROT (2) drops in distance and cannot be left out.",
